PUB_PUB_TITLE: Resolving phylogenetic and classical nomenclature: A revision of Seraphsidae Jung, 1974 (Gastropoda: Neostromboidae)
PUB_PUB_FORMATTED: Maxwell, S.J., Rymer, T.L., & Congdon, B.C. 2021. Resolving phylogenetic and classical nomenclature: A revision of Seraphsidae Jung, 1974 (Gastropoda: Neostromboidae). Zootaxa 4990: 401-453

QUALIFICATION: Tableau encyclopédique et méthodique des trois règnes de la nature. Partie 21, Mollusques testacés: pl. 360; No included species, but name available by indication (association to an illustration). Röding subsequently included three nominal species, and included Bulla terebellum in the synonymy of two of them. Neave, 1940, Nomenclator Zoologicus, 4: 426, listed Terebellum Bolten, 1798 and Terebellum Lamarck (non Bolten, 1798), 1798 as two different names. However, both Röding [1798, Museum Boltenianum, 2: 135] and Lamarck [1799, Mémoires de la Société d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris, (1799): 69] included Bulla terebellum, which clearly indicates that they applied the same name for the same taxonomical extension. See also Terebrina
